uage to another (e.g., Python Flask → Node.js Express, Python → Rust)\n- **Performance**: Claims to be 10x faster than traditional migration methods\n- **Features**:\n  - Smart dependency identification and conversion\n  - Automated Docker environment configuration\n  - Recursive codebase reconstruction from entry files\n  - Automatic unit test generation and validation\n  - Iterative debugging based on error logs and context\n\n### 2. **Vibe Coding - AI-Powered Migration Framework**\nA February 2026 article describes a real-world migration project using AI to move a CLI tool from Node.js to Rust:\n- **Methodology**: Combines human direction with AI implementation\n- **Process**: Used \"OpenSpec\" workflow (Proposal → Apply → Archive)\n- **Results**: Achieved specific performance targets (<10ms startup time, <10MB memory)\n- **Approach**: Broke migration into 21 specific tasks completed iteratively with AI assistance\n\n### 3. **Traditional AST-Based Tools with AI Enhancement**\nThe search results mention established migration tools that are being enhanced with AI:\n- **OpenRewrite**: For Java code batch migration\n- **gogocode**: For Vue single-file component migration\n- **jscodeshift**: Facebook's React API upgrade tool\n- **ast-grep**: Multi-language AST query and replacement\n\n**AI Integration**: These tools use AI to generate migration rules (rewrite.yml files) and handle complex business semantic migrations that pure pattern matching cannot handle.\n\n### 4. **AWS SDK Migration Tool**\nAWS provides a migration tool using OpenRewrite to automate migration from AWS SDK for Java 1.x to 2.x, though it's noted as a preview release with some limitations.\n\n## Context Note\nWhile the search results don't show specific new tools launched in February 2026, the content from January-February 2026 timeframe shows active development and practical application of AI migration tools, particularly GPT-Migrate and custom AI-assisted migration workflows.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MU