            "url": "https://m.toutiao.com/w/1856153420524675/"
          },
          {
            "title": "2026 年 1 月 GitHub 十大热门项目排行榜",
            "url": "http://juejin.cn/post/7602191709388292138"
          },
          {
            "title": "GitHub 过去 7 天 AI 项目飙升 TOP10 深度盘点（附开源地址 & 上手建议）",
            "url": "https://blog.csdn.net/qq_34252622/article/details/157552464"
          }
        ]
      },
      "# Search Results: Open Source AI Coding Agents & Self-Hosted AI Coding (February 2026)\n\nBased on the search results for February 2026, here are the key findings:\n\n## Top Open Source AI Coding Agent Projects\n\n### 1. **OpenCode** (85,901 stars)\n- **Repository**: https://github.com/anomalyco/opencode (Note: This appears to be a very popular open-source coding agent)\n- **Description**: \"The open source coding agent\"\n- **Key Features**:\n  - TUI (Terminal User Interface) focused, optimized for Neovim users\n  - Client-server architecture allowing remote operation\n  - Supports multiple LLMs (Claude, OpenAI, Google Gemini, local LLMs)\n  - Can complete code understanding, generation, modification, debugging, refactoring, and multi-step task planning\n  - 100% open source with MIT license\n  - Cross-platform desktop applications (macOS, Windows, Linux)\n\n### 2. **Qwen Code** (from Qwen3.5 release - February 16, 2026)\n- **Repository**: https://github.com/QwenLM/Qwen3.5\n- **Description**: Open-source AI agent for the terminal, optimized for Qwen models\n- **Features**: Helps understand large codebases, automate tedious work, and ship faster\n\n### 3. **Claude Code Plugins & Ecosystem**\nSeveral Claude-related projects trending:\n- **claude-mem** (23,680 stars): Auto-captures Claude coding sessions and compresses with AI for context injection\n- **Claude Code Alternatives**: Multiple CLI-based coding assistants emerging as alternatives\n\n## Notable Self-Hosted & Local-First AI Coding Tools\n\n### 1. **AionUi** (15.2k stars)\n- **Repository**: https://github.com/iOfficeAI/AionUi\n- Unified graphical interface for CLI AI tools (Gemini CLI, Claude Code, etc.)\n- Supports local models (Ollama) and multi-session parallel processing\n- Local data storage with SQLite for privacy\n\n### 2. **OpenClaw** (152k+ stars)\n- **Repository**: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw\n- Local-first personal AI assistant running on your device\n- Self-hosted with Docker support\n- Strong focus on privacy and local deployment\n\n### 3. **Goose** (29.6k stars)\n- **Repository**: https://github.com/block/goose\n- On-machine agent with high execution permissions\n- Can install dependencies, execute commands, edit files, and run tests\n- Supports MCP (Model Context Protocol) for extensibility\n\n## Key Trends in February 2026\n\n1. **MCP (Model Context Protocol) Standardization**: Multiple projects adopting MCP for cross-tool collaboration\n2. **Terminal/CLI-First Approach**: Strong preference for TUI-based agents (OpenCode, Claude Code)\n3. **Local & Privacy-First**: Major emphasis on self-hosted solutions with local data storage\n4. **Multi-Model Support**: Most tools support multiple LLM providers (not locked to single vendor)\n5. **Client-Server Architecture**: Enabling remote operation while running locally\n6. **Agent Autonomy**: Shift from code completion to full workflow automation (planning → editing → executing → testing)\n\n## Other Notable Mentions\n\n- **Tambo AI** (8,821 stars): Open-source generative UI SDK for React\n- **Chrome DevTools MCP** (24,3k stars): Browser automation for AI coding agents\n- **Browser-Use** (76,423 stars): AI browser automation framework for LLMs\n\nThe ecosystem is clearly moving toward **open-source, self-hosted, privacy-focused AI coding agents** that can run complex development workflows rather than just providing code suggestions."
