      "## Search Results: VS Code Extension OR JetBrains Plugin AI Coding - February 2026 Launch\n\nBased on the search results, I found relevant information about AI coding tools from JetBrains and their VS Code extensions. Here are the key findings:\n\n### Most Relevant Finding - February 2026 Announcement:\n\n**JetBrains Announces Free AI Tools Tier** (February 19, 2026)\n- JetBrains announced that all their AI tools (including the improved AI Assistant and new coding agent **Junie**) are now available through a single subscription in their IDEs with a **free tier**\n- The free tier provides unlimited code completion and local AI model access, plus cloud-based AI assistance with credit limits\n- Junie, the AI coding assistant, is now available to all JetBrains customers\n\n### Key Related Developments:\n\n**1. JetBrains AI Assistant for VS Code (2025)**\n- JetBrains released an AI Assistant extension for Visual Studio Code\n- Available from the VS Code Marketplace\n- Supports multiple programming languages (Java, Kotlin, JavaScript, TypeScript, Python, C#, C++, C, Go, PHP, Rust, Scala, Swift, R, Ruby, JSON, Shell)\n- Features include code completion, chat interface, code editing directly from chat, and AI coding agents\n- Uses Mellum (JetBrains' LLM optimized for coding)\n- Currently in public preview\n\n**2. Junie AI Agent (April 2025)**\n- JetBrains introduced Junie, an AI agent capable of handling multi-step tasks including code writing and debugging\n- Offered as part of the 2025.1 IDEs release\n- Available for IntelliJ IDEA Ultimate, PyCharm Pro, WebStorm, and GoLand (with more IDEs coming soon)\n\n**3. OpenAI Codex Integration (January 2026)**\n- OpenAI's AI programming tool Codex officially launched on JetBrains development tools\n- Available as an extension plugin for IntelliJ IDEA, PyCharm, WebStorm, and Rider\n- Based on GPT-5.2 Codex model\n- Currently in limited-time free promotional period\n\n### Summary:\nWhile the search didn't return a specific result for a \"February 2026 launch\" of a VS Code extension or JetBrains plugin, it did reveal that JetBrains made a significant announcement in **February 2026** about making their AI tools (including Junie AI agent and AI Assistant) available with a **free tier** across all their IDEs. The JetBrains AI Assistant for VS Code had already launched in 2025 and is currently in public preview."
