el\n- **Qwen3-Coder-Plus** - Latest code generation model\n- **Qwen3-Coder-Next** - Advanced coding model\n- **Third-party models**: GLM-4.7, Kimi-K2.5\n\n### **Request Quota**\n- **90,000 requests per month**\n\n### **Compatible AI Tools**\nOpen ecosystem approach supporting:\n- Qwen Code\n- Claude Code\n- Cline\n- Cursor\n- OpenClaw/Moltbot\n- (Compatible with OpenAI/Anthropic API specifications)\n\n### **Pricing**\n- **New customers**: First month for **¥7.9** (Lite basic package)\n- **Existing customers**: 50% discount on renewal\n- Available from February 19, 2026 to April 1, 2026 (UTC+8)\n\n## 🔑 Core Advantages\n\n1. **Open Ecosystem**: Unlike competitors (OpenAI's Codex locked in ChatGPT, Google's AlphaCode only on Vertex AI), Qwen opens its protocol and interfaces to third-party tools\n\n2. **Flexibility**: Users can work in their preferred environments (VS Code, JetBrains) without switching tools\n\n3. **Data Compliance**: Addresses enterprise needs for data compliance and transparency, avoiding the \"black box\" approach\n\n4. **Cost-Effective**: Qwen3.5-Plus API priced at **¥0.8 per million tokens** - less than 5% of comparable models like Gemini 3\n\n5. **Seamless Integration**: No need to change subscriptions or configurations when switching between supported models\n\n## 🎯 Strategic Positioning\nThis launch represents a shift in strategy - from competing on model strength alone to enabling **model integration into existing developer workflows**. This approach specifically targets developers frustrated with vendor lock-in, rising GitHub Copilot prices, and data compliance issues with US-based services.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
